FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1772110991
OL,3,CHeadline gig for musician told she
OL,4,Cwouldn't be able to walk again
OL,6,FBut, just four years later Lauren,
OL,7,Ffrom Clitheroe in Lancashire, is
OL,8,Fpursuing her dream - writing and
OL,9,Fperforming her music to growing
OL,10,Faudiences.
OL,12,FLauren said her stroke was
OL,13,F"terrifying", leaving her unable to
OL,14,Fstand, her vision blurred and
OL,15,Fultimately leading to her being
OL,16,Fairlifted from a Spanish hospital back
OL,17,Fto the UK.
OL,19,FAt this point, medics warned the
OL,20,Fteenager she may never walk, talk or
OL,21,Fplay her beloved instruments again.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1772110991
OL,3,CHeadline gig for musician told she
OL,4,Cwouldn't be able to walk again
OL,6,FThe 21-year-old is proving medics
OL,7,Fwrong, working full-time in music,
OL,8,Fmastering more instruments and music
OL,9,Fproduction.
OL,11,F"I was told I won't be able to play
OL,12,Fthe instrument again," she said.
OL,14,F"I got told I'd never be able to walk
OL,15,Fagain. And then last year, I've made
OL,16,Fsinging in my full time job and played
OL,17,Finstruments every day.
OL,19,F"And I ran the London Marathon. So I'm
OL,20,Fwalking and playing again, and I won't
OL,21,Fchange it."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
